    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-10-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-10-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="139"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d139">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89 Roumania/17</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Rumanian Chargé</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Nano</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Roumanian Chargé d’Affaires <hi rend="italic">ad interim</hi> presents his
                    compliments to the Secretary of State and pursuant to his note of October 18th,
                    No. 4415/2,<note n="34" xml:id="d139fn34">Not printed.</note> has the honor to
                    state that his Government has designated Mr. Eftimie Antonesco, counsellor of
                    the Roumanian Supreme Court (Cour de Cassation), formerly technical delegate to
                    the Paris Conference and the conferences of Vienna and Rome, and Mr. Antoniade,
                    formerly Secretary General of the Ministry of Justice and now president of the
                    Commission for the Consolidation of Treasury Bonds in Paris, to conduct the
                    proposed negotiations concerning the indebtedness of Roumania to the United
                    States, and that they will shortly proceed to Washington.</p>
                <pb facs="0536" n="416" xml:id="pg_416"/>
                <p>It appears, therefore, that Mr. Filitti’s appointment has been cancelled.<note
                        n="35" xml:id="d139fn35">The Rumanian Chargé in his note of Oct. 18 had
                        stated that Mr. Filitti had been designated to conduct the debt
                        negotiations.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-10-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 20, 1922</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>No. 4446/2.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
